#week-title("Two", "Electional Astrology & Laboratory Beginnings")

=== Core Teaching

*Electional Astrology* — the choosing of auspicious moments for beginning major
operations — is introduced this week as a practical discipline.

Major laboratory beginnings, such as the sealing of a digestion flask, the start
of a long circulation, or the first fire under a mineral preparation, all
benefit from chosen moments. By electing the "birth" of a preparation, the
alchemist aligns the work with the cosmic forces that will govern its evolution.

=== Topics This Week

- Basics of Electional Astrology
- Choosing auspicious moments for laboratory operations
- The "Birth" of a preparation: why the start time matters
- Tracking planetary medicine through Herbs and Stars

#inner-work[
  *The Moment of Beginning*

  Reflect on a major project you have started in the past (alchemical or
  otherwise). Do you remember the "feel" of the moment it began?

  As you prepare to start a new long maceration or circulation this month,
  select a specific day and hour based on your chart and the planetary hours.
  Record the elected time and your mental state at that moment in your journal.
]

